#: src/rust-2018/error-handling-and-panics/aborting-on-panic.md:1
msgid "Aborting on panic"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/error-handling-and-panics/aborting-on-panic.md:3
msgid ""
"![Minimum Rust version: 1.10](https://img.shields.io/badge/"
"Minimum%20Rust%20Version-1.10-brightgreen.svg)"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/error-handling-and-panics/aborting-on-panic.md:5
msgid ""
"By default, Rust programs will unwind the stack when a `panic!` happens. If "
"you'd prefer an immediate abort instead, you can configure this in `Cargo."
"toml`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/error-handling-and-panics/aborting-on-panic.md:8
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[profile.debug]\n"
"panic = \"abort\"\n"
"\n"
"[profile.release]\n"
"panic = \"abort\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/error-handling-and-panics/aborting-on-panic.md:16
msgid ""
"Why might you choose to do this? By removing support for unwinding, you'll "
"get smaller binaries. You will lose the ability to catch panics. Which "
"choice is right for you depends on exactly what you're doing."
msgstr ""
